I see that you understood. For a minute I thought you were right, but this is rather confusing, indeed.

Observe line 1163: the last OTNS reported state to get in this function should be OT_RADIO_STATE_TRANSMIT:
```    otEXPECT(sLastReportedState == OT_RADIO_STATE_TRANSMIT);```

So, if a device is in OT_RADIO_STATE_RECEIVE and receives a packet, it might send an ACK. However, during this ACK transmission, it will not change its own state to "transmiting", instead It keeps on OT_RADIO_STATE_RECEIVE. So, for OTNS accuracy, we did already report a change anyway for this ACK at line 1221
```
// Radio sState keeps in OT_RADIO_STATE_RECEIVE even when sending an ack.
// For energy accuracy, we make a report without changing the sState.
reportRadioStatusToOtns(OT_RADIO_STATE_TRANSMIT);
```

So, now we just need to fix it back with line 1179
```
// Radio sState keeps in OT_RADIO_STATE_RECEIVE even when sending an ack.
// For energy accuracy, we make a report without changing the sState.
if (otMacFrameIsAckRequested(&sTransmitFrame))
{
    reportRadioStatusToOtns(OT_RADIO_STATE_RECEIVE);
}
```

