I'm having a really hard time understanding this function. It's too long, but more importantly there are too many levels of nesting. I think it will be difficult for other developers to make changes here without introducing bugs.

At a high level what you're trying to do here is map toolkits to result processing logic. I would recommend creating a separate function for each top level code block. 

Also rather than lots of complicated top level if/elif-statements, it's probably cleaner to do that mapping with a dictionary. 

To make it cleaner, I would recommend restructuring the top level function to look something like this:
```python
@app.route('/predict', methods=['GET', 'POST'])
def model_predict():
    TOOLKIT_TO_PROCESSING_FUNCTION = {
        tc.toolkits.image_classifier.image_classifier.ImageClassifier: processing1,
        tc.toolkits.style_transfer.style_transfer.StyleTransfer: processing2,
        ......
        ......
    }

    model_type = type(model)
    if model_type not in TOOLKIT_TO_PROCESSING_FUNCTION:
        return_success({"error": "Unimplemented Toolkit"}, False)

    result = TOOLKIT_TO_PROCESSING_FUNCTION[model_type]()
    return_success(result, True)
}

